UPDATE public.forum_threads
SET title = 'FanRealms Game Jam #1 — $100 Prize Pool',
    content = E'# FanRealms Game Jam #1\n\n**Prize Pool: $100 · Duration: 1 Week**\n\nWelcome to the first FanRealms Game Jam. Build a small indie game over the course of a week and share it with the community.\n\n---\n\n## Prizes\n\n| Place | Prize |\n|-------|-------|\n| 1st | $60 |\n| 2nd | $30 |\n| 3rd | $10 |\n\nPrizes paid via Cash App.\n\n---\n\n## Theme\n\nOpen theme — make any indie game you want. Any genre, any art style, any engine.\n\n---\n\n## Rules\n\n1. Game must be made during the jam period (1 week).\n2. Solo or team — any size, anyone can join.\n3. Any engine is allowed (Godot, Unity, Pygame, etc.).\n4. Submit your game on the Games page (https://fanrealms.com/games) and reply to this thread with the link.\n5. Free or pay-what-you-want only — no paid entries.\n6. Pre-made assets are allowed, but the game itself must be made during the jam.\n\n---\n\n## Schedule\n\n- Start: TBA — watch this thread for the official start announcement.\n- Submissions close: 1 week after start.\n- Winners announced: within 48 hours of submissions closing.\n\n---\n\n## Judging\n\nCommunity vote — the submission with the most replies/upvotes in this thread wins. In the event of a tie, the FanRealms team breaks it.\n\n---\n\n## How to Submit\n\n1. Build your game and host it somewhere playable (itch.io, a hosted web build, a downloadable zip, etc.).\n2. Add it to the FanRealms Games page using the external link.\n3. Reply to this thread with the link and a short description.\n\nNo file upload is required — the Games page accepts an external URL to your build.\n\n---\n\nQuestions? Reply below or email jake.yanouyang@gmail.com.\n\nGood luck.'
WHERE id = '7e40e6ad-bc74-45c2-bd99-dd81128646b4';